Nguyen Thuy Khanh is a Fresher Full-Stack Developer, demonstrating foundational full-stack development skills through academic projects. Their core expertise encompasses architectural patterns like Microservices, Layered Architecture, and MVC, coupled with security techniques such as OAuth 2.0, OpenID Connect, and JWT. Through projects like 'Fixora Shop' and 'Jewelry Shop,' they have gained practical experience in developing comprehensive web applications with role-based features, streamlining e-commerce operations, customer management, order processing, product management, payment processing, and feedback systems, often leveraging centralized administrative dashboards. These projects utilized key frameworks including Spring Boot, React, and Laravel.
Technically, Nguyen Thuy Khanh is proficient in programming languages such as Java, PHP, JavaScript, HTML, and CSS. They possess hands-on experience with modern frameworks and libraries including Spring Boot, Laravel, React, React Router, Axios, and Redux. Database management skills cover MySQL, SQL Server, and H2 Console. For development tooling and version control, they are adept with Git, GitHub, IntelliJ IDEA, and VS Code. Their project experience has provided exposure to domain knowledge in e-commerce systems, encompassing user authentication, shopping cart functionality, order management, payment integration, and administrative oversight.